      <a name="top"></a>
      <h1>Blackboard</h1>
      <h2>Learning Management System</h2>
      
      <ul class="anchors">
        	<li><a href="#addstudents">Can I add students to my site who aren't enrolled?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#roles">Available Course Site Roles</a></li>
          	<li><a href="#incomplete">Enroll a Student in a Course Site to Finish an Incomplete</a></li>  	
          	<li><a href="#addusers">Adding Users to Blackboard Course Sites</a></li>
            <li><a href="#organization">Adding Users to Blackboard Organization Sites</a></li>
            
        </ul>
      <hr />
      <h4><a name="addstudents"></a>&quot;Can I add students to my site who aren't enrolled?&quot;</h4>
      <p>Instructors cannot enroll students in a course site.</p>
      <p>Enrollment in Blackboard course sites is Pathway-driven. When a student enrolls in a course through Pathway, the student is added to the Blackboard course site within 1 business day following their enrollment in Pathway.</p>

      <p>Instructors can request that students be <a href="#incomplete">enrolled in a course site to finish an incomplete</a>. Instructors can also <a href="#addusers">request that teaching assistants, instructors, graders and course builders be given access to a course site</a>. </p>
      <p><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>
      <hr/>
      
      <h4><a name="roles"></a>Available Course Site Roles</h4>
      <ul><li>Teaching Assistants</li>
        <li>Instructors</li>
        <li>Graders</li>
        <li>Course Builders</li>
      </ul>
      <h4><a name="incomplete"></a>Enroll a Student in a Course Site to Finish an Incomplete</h4>
      <p>If an instructor needs to  give a student access to a course site in order to finish an incomplete, the  instructor must email the Registrar’s office at <a href="mailto:registrar@umkc.edu">registrar@umkc.edu</a>. The Registrar’s office will then authorize Instructional Technologies Services to enroll the student in the course site.</p>
      <p><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>
      <hr/>
      
      <h4><a name="addusers"></a>Adding Users to Blackboard Course Sites</h4>
      <p>Note: If you are enrolling many users at one time, use the Batch Enrollment Template listed below and follow the instructions detailed in the Batch Enrollments PDF.</p>
      <ul>
<li>Enrolling Instructors, TAs, Course Builders, and Graders to a Blackboard Course Site | <a href="documents/Instructors/Enrollment/addingtagraders.pdf">PDF</a></li>
